record_data.record_plain_text: KMC THERMO, LLC Market-Based Rate Tariff 1. Availability. KMC Thermo, LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy and capacity in the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") Balancing Authority Area ("BAA") available under this tariff to any purchasers with whom it has contracts, except as prohibited below. Seller also makes available, except as prohibited below, to any purchasers, the ancillary services in the PJM BAA listed in this Paragraph 1. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 2. Applicability. This tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity, or ancillary services by Seller that are: (a) subject to the Commission's jurisdiction; and (b) are not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Seller on file with the Commission. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 5. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Sales under this tariff shall be limited to the PJM BAA. Seller has received (i) waiver of the accounting and reporting requirements contained in 18 C.F.R. Parts 41, 101, with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects, and 141, except Sections 141.14 and 141.15; (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subparts B and C, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket authorization for the issuance of securities and the assumption of liabilities under 18 C.F.R. Part 34. KMC Thermo, LLC, Docket No. ER14-1468-001 (May 14, 2014) (unpublished letter order). 8. Effective Date. This tariff is effective upon the date specified by the Commission.

KMC THERMO, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2 REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
KMC Thermo, LLC ("KMC Thermo") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power Service") from a natural gas-fueled electric generating facility located in Prince George's County, Maryland ("Facility") in the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule FERC No. 2 sets forth KMC Thermo's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Power Service from the Facility to PJM, or to an entity authorized to resell such service to PJM, as provided by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $790,000.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $790,000 / 12 = $65,833.33.
LOST OPPORTUNITY COST CHARGE:
By means of the Lost Opportunity Cost Charge, KMC Thermo may receive revenues for lost opportunity costs associated with the Facility calculated and distributed in accordance with Section 3.2.3B of Schedule 1 of the Amended and Restated Operating Agreement of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., as amended from time to time.

record_data.record_plain_text: KMC THERMO, LLC Market-Based Rate Tariff 1. Availability. KMC Thermo, LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services in the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") Balancing Authority Area ("BAA") available under this tariff to any purchasers with whom it has contracts, except as prohibited in the balancing authority area of El Paso Electric Company ("EPE") as described further below. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 2. Applicability. This tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity, or ancillary services by Seller that are: (a) subject to the Commission's jurisdiction; and (b) are not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Seller on file with the Commission. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 5. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Sales under this tariff shall be limited to the PJM BAA. Seller has received (i) waiver of the accounting and reporting requirements contained in 18 C.F.R. Part 41, Part 101, with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects, and Part 141, except Sections 141.14 and 141.15; (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subparts B and C, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket authorization for the issuance of securities and the assumption of liabilities under 18 C.F.R. Part 34. KMC Thermo, LLC, Docket No. ER14-1468-001 (May 14, 2014) (unpublished letter order). Seller may not make sales of capacity, energy, and/or ancillary services within the balancing authority area of EPE, where EPE does not have market-based rate authority for sales within its balancing authority area. See El Paso Electric Company, 87 FERC 61,219 (1999); Mankato Energy Center, LLC, et al., 185 FERC 61,134 (2023). 8. Mitigated Sales. Sales of energy and capacity are permissible under this tariff in all balancing authority areas where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority. Sales of energy and capacity under this tariff are also permissible at the metered boundary between the Seller's mitigated balancing authority area (the EPE balancing authority area) and a balancing authority area where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority provided: (i) legal title of the power sold transfers at the metered boundary of the balancing authority area where the Seller has market-based rate authority; and (ii) if the Seller sells at the metered boundary of a mitigated balancing authority area at market-based rates, then neither it nor its affiliates can sell into that mitigated balancing authority area from the outside. Seller must retain, for a period of five years from the date of the sale, all data and information related to the sale that demonstrates compliance with items (i) and (ii) above. 9. Effective Date. This tariff is effective upon the date specified by the Commission.
